SECTION:CLICK_ANALYSIS_STRATEGY — How to effectively analyze clicks
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

>>STRATEGY{id:CLICK-AUDIT, type:behavioral_verification}
  ::problem: "O que esta acontecendo vs o que deveria acontecer"
  ::methodology:
    1. TRACE: Mapear todos os event listeners por componente
    2. SEQUENCE: Documentar a cadeia de handler calls
    3. STATE: Verificar estado antes/durante/depois do click
    4. SIDE_EFFECTS: Verificar API calls, localStorage, context updates
    5. VISUAL: Screenshot/diff antes e depois
  ::tools: [browser_devtools_event_listeners,console.trace,ReactDevTools_profiler,Playwright_trace_viewer]

>>CLICK_MAP{component:ChangelogBadge}
  ::trigger: click no sino (Bell/BellRing)
  ::expected_flow: toggle panel -> fetch entries -> render lista -> mark unread
  ::actual_flow: toggle panel -> render entries from props -> handleClickOutside fecha
  ::risks:
    - z-index conflito RESOLVIDO (v3.6.0 changelog-notification-bell-fix)
    - stopPropagation adicionado
    - createPortal usa document.body, pode causar re-render fora do React tree
  ::verificar:
    - onMarkAsRead chamado 2x? (linha 210 onclick do card + botao separado)
    - isUnread callback vindo de useChangelog via props
    - Panel position calculated from buttonRef.getBoundingClientRect

>>CLICK_MAP{component:LunaFloatingButton}
  ::trigger: click ou drag (onPointerDown/Move/Up)
  ::expected_flow: click -> toggle chat panel. drag -> move button. no toggle on drag.
  ::actual_flow: pointerDown sets drag=false. pointerMove sets drag=true. pointerUp: if !didDrag -> toggle. if didDrag -> snap to edge.
  ::risks:
    - pointer capture removido no v3.6.1 (changelog-luna-draggable-click-fix)
    - didDrag guard funciona mas threshold nao documentado
    - localStorage persistence: position stored as JSON
    - F5 reseta posicao? Nao, restaura do localStorage
  ::verificar:
    - onClick nao eh usado diretamente, so pointerUp. Pode haver delay no mobile.
    - Chat panel open state vem de onde? Provavelmente LunaContext ou state local
    - Z-index do chat panel vs outros modais

>>CLICK_MAP{component:SecretTerminal}
  ::trigger: sequencia de teclas ou botao secreto
  ::expected_flow: abre terminal camuflado -> permite comandos admin
  ::actual_flow: captura camera e screenshot em tentativa login falha
  ::risks:
    - getUserMedia pode falhar silenciosamente se permissao negada
    - getDisplayMedia pode mostrar picker ao usuario (nao eh silencioso)
    - Payload base64 pode ser muito grande (10MB limit no express.json)
    - Imagens enviadas para Discord webhook — privacidade?

>>CLICK_MAP{component:TaskComments}
  ::trigger: digitar @ -> dropdown usuarios
  ::expected_flow: @ -> checkMentions -> dropdown -> click usuario -> insert mention -> highlight
  ::actual_flow: timing bug corrigido no v3.6.0 (changelog-task-mentions)
  ::risks:
    - Backend extrai mentions[] mas como usa? Apenas para Discord webhook?
    - Mapeamento de usuario para Discord ID: hardcoded ou configuravel?

>>CLICK_MAP{component:NotificationCenter}
  ::trigger: click no sino (TopBar) ou push notification
  ::expected_flow: abre drawer com notificacoes -> click marca lida -> badge atualiza
  ::actual_flow: useNotifications hook -> polling /api/notifications -> ToastContext para toasts
  ::risks:
    - Duplicacao de funcionalidade com ChangelogBadge? Ambos tem sino.
    - NotificationCenter vs ChangelogBadge: qual aparece no TopBar?
    - Conflito visual se ambos renderizarem badges

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
SECTION:ARCHITECTURE_DEBT — Structural problems that will explode
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

>>DEBT{id:DEBT-001, severity:CRITICAL, type:data_persistence}
  ::name: JSON Fallback Hybrid
  ::desc: backend/datastore.js permite USE_PG=false, gravando em JSON files
  ::impact: Corrupcao de dados, race conditions, sem ACID, backups impossiveis
  ::fix: ELIMINAR fallback. Se DATABASE_URL nao existe, backend ENCERRA.
  ::roadmap_ref: FASE_0_TAREFA_0.1

>>DEBT{id:DEBT-002, severity:CRITICAL, type:code_organization}
  ::name: Monolith server.js (354KB, 8796 lines)
  ::desc: Toda logica de negocio em um arquivo. Impossivel testar, manter, ou onboard.
  ::impact: Mudanca em uma rota pode quebrar outra. Merge conflicts constantes.
  ::fix: Clean Architecture — domain -> application -> infrastructure -> interface
  ::roadmap_ref: FASE_1_TAREFA_1.1

>>DEBT{id:DEBT-003, severity:HIGH, type:language_consistency}
  ::name: 15% TypeScript, 85% JavaScript
  ::desc: Frontend tem TSX/TS misturado com JSX. Backend 100% JS.
  ::impact: Type errors em runtime. Null/undefined bugs frequentes.
  ::fix: Migrar backend para TS strict. Frontend 100% TS.
  ::roadmap_ref: FASE_0_TAREFA_0.2

>>DEBT{id:DEBT-004, severity:HIGH, type:testing}
  ::name: 0% Test Coverage
  ::desc: Nenhum teste unitario, integracao, ou E2E encontrado.
  ::impact: Bugs so detectados em producao. Refatoracao impossivel sem medo.
  ::fix: Jest + Supertest + Playwright. Cobertura 70% minimo.
  ::roadmap_ref: FASE_0_TAREFA_0.3

>>DEBT{id:DEBT-005, severity:HIGH, type:ai_dependency}
  ::name: Gemini API Unica Fonte de LLM
  ::desc: Sem fallback local robusto. NLU offline existe mas e muito limitada.
  ::impact: Quando API cai, Luna fica cega. Taxa 25% sucesso no chat.
  ::fix: Ollama integration (llama3.1:8b) + circuit breaker + RAG.
  ::roadmap_ref: FASE_3_TAREFA_3.1

>>DEBT{id:DEBT-006, severity:MEDIUM, type:frontend_performance}
  ::name: No Code Splitting
  ::desc: App.jsx importa todas as paginas estaticamente. Bundle unico.
  ::impact: First load lento em mobile. Lighthouse score baixo.
  ::fix: React.lazy + Suspense por rota. Bundle <500KB inicial.
  ::roadmap_ref: FASE_4_TAREFA_4.1

>>DEBT{id:DEBT-007, severity:MEDIUM, type:state_management}
  ::name: Context Hell + Prop Drilling
  ::desc: Multiplos contexts (Auth,Toast,Luna,EmailFocus,EmailDensity) sem normalizacao.
  ::impact: Re-renders desnecessarios. Dificil rastrear origem de estado.
  ::fix: Zustand ou Redux Toolkit para estado global. Contexts apenas para injecao de dependencia.
  ::roadmap_ref: FUTURO

